-- BAM sells U.S. business, hikes 2007 targets
-- 
-- Tue Sep 25, 2007 5:45am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/25/businesspro-bam-dc-idUSWEB797820070925

 

 AMSTERDAM  (Reuters) - Dutch builder Royal BAM Groep 
( BAMN.AS ) said on Tuesday it is selling its U.S. subsidiary 
Flatiron Construction Corp for 172 million euros ($242.7 
million) to Germany's Hochtief AG ( HOTG.DE ) and raised its 2007 
sales and profit targets. 

  BAM, the largest Dutch construction group, said it will 
book a profit of about 70 million euros on the sale of 
Flatiron.  BAM also revised its 2007 outlook, saying it expects 9 
billion euros in sales for 2007 and a net profit of at least 
296 million euros, including the book profit.